    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"ðŸ”— link\"\ndescription: \"link is a simple R ðŸ“¦ that makes it easier to include links to packages pkgdown pages\"\nauthor:\n  - name: Romain FranÃ§ois\n    affiliation: tadaâ¬¢science\n    affiliation-url: https://tada.science\ndate: 2024-02-17\ncategories: [R, package, link]\nimage: logo.png\ncitation: \n  url: https://tada.science/posts/2024-02-26-link\ndraft: false\n---\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n<template></template>\n\n</bslib-tooltip>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n<img src=\"logo.png\" align=\"left\" height=\"138\" style=\"margin: 10px\"/>\n\n<bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>Hyperlink Automatic Detection â€¢ link</template>\n  <a href=\"https://link.tada.science/\" class=\"r-link-pkg\" target=\"_blank\">link</a>\n</bslib-tooltip> is a simple goofy R ðŸ“¦ that makes it simple to include links to packages, e.g. <bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>Easily Install and Load the Tidyverse â€¢ tidyverse</template>\n  <a href=\"https://tidyverse.tidyverse.org\" class=\"r-link-pkg\" target=\"_blank\">tidyverse</a>\n</bslib-tooltip>, <bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>A Grammar of Data Manipulation â€¢ dplyr</template>\n  <a href=\"https://dplyr.tidyverse.org\" class=\"r-link-pkg\" target=\"_blank\">dplyr</a>\n</bslib-tooltip> and function calls <bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>Summarise each group down to one row â€” summarise â€¢ dplyr</template>\n  <a href=\"https://dplyr.tidyverse.org/reference/summarise.html\" class=\"r-link-call\" target=\"_blank\">summarise()</a>\n</bslib-tooltip> <bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>Create a new ggplot â€” ggplot â€¢ ggplot2</template>\n  <a href=\"https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/ggplot.html\" class=\"r-link-call\" target=\"_blank\">ggplot()</a>\n</bslib-tooltip> in your `.Rmd` or `.qmd` files.\n\nThis works by setting the <bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>knitr - Elegant, flexible, and fast dynamic report generation with R  - Yihui Xie | è°¢ç›Šè¾‰</template>\n  <a href=\"https://yihui.org/knitr/\" class=\"r-link-pkg\" target=\"_blank\">knitr</a>\n</bslib-tooltip> `text` hook with <bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>Setup automatic linking â€” to_pkg â€¢ link</template>\n  <a href=\"http://link.tada.science/reference/auto.html\" class=\"r-link-call\" target=\"_blank\">auto()</a>\n</bslib-tooltip> somewhere in your document. You can learn more about <bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>knitr - Elegant, flexible, and fast dynamic report generation with R  - Yihui Xie | è°¢ç›Šè¾‰</template>\n  <a href=\"https://yihui.org/knitr/\" class=\"r-link-pkg\" target=\"_blank\">knitr</a>\n</bslib-tooltip> hooks in the [Writing knitr hooks](https://blog.djnavarro.net/posts/2023-12-30_knitr-hooks/) article from Danielle Navarro's [Notes from a data witch](https://blog.djnavarro.net) blog.\n\n````         \n```{r}\n#| echo: false\nlink::auto(keep_braces = FALSE, keep_pkg_prefix = FALSE)\n```\n````\n\nThe defaults `keep_braces = TRUE` and `keep_pkg_prefix` keeps the braces around the ðŸ“¦ names and the package prefix in the calls. This is popular style but I don't like it and find it too noisy.\n\n<bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>Hyperlink Automatic Detection â€¢ link</template>\n  <a href=\"https://link.tada.science/\" class=\"r-link-pkg\" target=\"_blank\">link</a>\n</bslib-tooltip> is heavily based on <bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>Syntax Highlighting and Automatic Linking â€¢ downlit</template>\n  <a href=\"https://downlit.r-lib.org/\" class=\"r-link-pkg\" target=\"_blank\">downlit</a>\n</bslib-tooltip> and especially <bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>Generate url for topic/article/package â€” href_topic â€¢ downlit</template>\n  <a href=\"https://downlit.r-lib.org/reference/href_topic.html\" class=\"r-link-call\" target=\"_blank\">href_package()</a>\n</bslib-tooltip> and <bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>Automatically link inline code â€” autolink â€¢ downlit</template>\n  <a href=\"https://downlit.r-lib.org/reference/autolink.html\" class=\"r-link-call\" target=\"_blank\">autolink()</a>\n</bslib-tooltip> which do the actual work. We just go the extra mile and make this automatic by means of a <bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>knitr - Elegant, flexible, and fast dynamic report generation with R  - Yihui Xie | è°¢ç›Šè¾‰</template>\n  <a href=\"https://yihui.org/knitr/\" class=\"r-link-pkg\" target=\"_blank\">knitr</a>\n</bslib-tooltip> hook.\n\nThis very article uses <bslib-tooltip placement=\"auto\" bsOptions=\"[]\" data-require-bs-version=\"5\" data-require-bs-caller=\"tooltip()\">\n  <template>Setup automatic linking â€” to_pkg â€¢ link</template>\n  <a href=\"http://link.tada.science/reference/auto.html\" class=\"r-link-call\" target=\"_blank\">auto()</a>\n</bslib-tooltip>, i.e. here is how it looks in rstudio:\n\n![](article.png){fig-align=\"center\" width=\"492\"}\n",
